Note:
Comprehensive Test Suite for NUMA Support Module

Tests all functionality of the NUMA (Non-Uniform Memory Access) support system including:
- Real NUMA topology detection via OS APIs across Linux, Windows, and macOS platforms
- Cross-platform memory binding with actual OS system calls and validation
- Memory interleaving with bandwidth optimization and performance monitoring
- NUMA-aware memory migration with cost calculation and efficiency analysis
- Performance monitoring and distance matrix computation for optimization
- Thread-safe operations with proper error handling and resource management
- Graceful degradation on non-NUMA systems with fallback mechanisms
- Production-ready enterprise-grade NUMA support with comprehensive validation
- AI/agent-friendly NUMA APIs for intelligent memory management
:End Note

Import "../../../../../../src/stdlib/advanced/memory/numa_support" as NUMASupport
Import "../../../../../../src/stdlib/advanced/utilities/common" as Common

Note: Test Configuration Constants
Let TEST_NODE_COUNT be 4
Let TEST_MEMORY_MB be 1024
Let TEST_CPU_COUNT be 8
Let TEST_BANDWIDTH_MB_PER_SEC be 1000
Let TEST_LATENCY_NS be 100
Let TEST_MIGRATION_THRESHOLD be 1000
Let TEST_ALLOCATION_SIZE_MB be 64

Note: Test Result Tracking
Let test_results be Dictionary[String, Boolean] containing
Let test_count be 0
Let passed_count be 0
Let failed_count be 0

Note: Helper Functions for Testing

Process called "run_test" that takes test_name as String and test_function as Function returns Boolean:
    Set test_count to test_count plus 1
    
    Try:
        Display message "Running test: " plus test_name
        Let result be test_function()
        
        If result:
            Set passed_count to passed_count plus 1
            Set test_results[test_name] to true
            Display message "  ✓ PASS: " plus test_name
        Otherwise:
            Set failed_count to failed_count plus 1
            Set test_results[test_name] to false
            Display message "  ✗ FAIL: " plus test_name
            
        Return result
        
    Catch error:
        Set failed_count to failed_count plus 1
        Set test_results[test_name] to false
        Display message "  ✗ ERROR: " plus test_name plus " - " plus convert_to_string with value as error
        Return false

Process called "assert_equals" that takes actual as Any and expected as Any and message as String returns Boolean:
    If actual is equal to expected:
        Return true
    Otherwise:
        Display message "  Assertion failed: " plus message
        Display message "    Expected: " plus convert_to_string with value as expected
        Display message "    Actual: " plus convert_to_string with value as actual
        Return false

Process called "assert_not_none" that takes value as Any and message as String returns Boolean:
    If value is not None:
        Return true
    Otherwise:
        Display message "  Assertion failed: " plus message plus " - value is None"
        Return false

Process called "assert_true" that takes value as Boolean and message as String returns Boolean:
    If value is true:
        Return true
    Otherwise:
        Display message "  Assertion failed: " plus message plus " - expected true, got false"
        Return false

Process called "assert_false" that takes value as Boolean and message as String returns Boolean:
    If value is false:
        Return true
    Otherwise:
        Display message "  Assertion failed: " plus message plus " - expected false, got true"
        Return false

Process called "assert_greater_than" that takes actual as Number and expected as Number and message as String returns Boolean:
    If actual is greater than expected:
        Return true
    Otherwise:
        Display message "  Assertion failed: " plus message
        Display message "    Expected > " plus convert_to_string with value as expected
        Display message "    Actual: " plus convert_to_string with value as actual
        Return false

Process called "assert_less_than" that takes actual as Number and expected as Number and message as String returns Boolean:
    If actual is less than expected:
        Return true
    Otherwise:
        Display message "  Assertion failed: " plus message
        Display message "    Expected < " plus convert_to_string with value as expected
        Display message "    Actual: " plus convert_to_string with value as actual
        Return false

Process called "assert_contains" that takes collection as List[Any] and item as Any and message as String returns Boolean:
    If collection contains item:
        Return true
    Otherwise:
        Display message "  Assertion failed: " plus message
        Display message "    Collection does not contain: " plus convert_to_string with value as item
        Return false

Process called "create_test_numa_node" that takes node_id as Integer returns NUMASupport.NUMANode:
    Note: Creates a test NUMA node for testing
    Return NUMASupport.NUMANode with:
        node_id as node_id
        cpus as list containing (node_id multiplied by 2), (node_id multiplied by 2 plus 1)
        memory_mb as TEST_MEMORY_MB
        distance_matrix as list containing 10, 20, 30, 40
        bandwidth_mb_per_sec as TEST_BANDWIDTH_MB_PER_SEC
        latency_ns as TEST_LATENCY_NS
        available_memory_mb as TEST_MEMORY_MB minus 128
        free_memory_mb as TEST_MEMORY_MB minus 256
        active as true
        metadata as dictionary containing
            "test_node" as true
            "created_at" as Common.get_current_timestamp

Process called "create_test_numa_topology" returns NUMASupport.NUMATopology:
    Note: Creates a test NUMA topology for testing
    Let nodes be list containing
    For i from 0 to (TEST_NODE_COUNT minus 1):
        Add create_test_numa_node with node_id as i to nodes
    
    Return NUMASupport.NUMATopology with:
        nodes as nodes
        total_nodes as TEST_NODE_COUNT
        numa_available as true
        operating_system as "test_os"
        cpu_count as TEST_CPU_COUNT
        total_memory_mb as TEST_MEMORY_MB multiplied by TEST_NODE_COUNT
        interleave_policy as "round_robin"
        detection_time as Common.get_current_timestamp
        metadata as dictionary containing
            "test_topology" as true

Process called "create_test_memory_block" that takes node_id as Integer and size_mb as Integer returns NUMASupport.MemoryBlock:
    Note: Creates a test memory block for NUMA testing
    Return NUMASupport.MemoryBlock with:
        address as 1000000 plus (node_id multiplied by 1000000)
        size_mb as size_mb
        node_id as node_id
        allocated_time as Common.get_current_timestamp
        access_count as 0
        last_access_time as Common.get_current_timestamp
        numa_local as true
        metadata as dictionary containing
            "test_block" as true

Note: NUMA Topology Detection Tests

Process called "test_operating_system_detection":
    Note: Tests operating system detection for NUMA support
    Let detected_os be NUMASupport.get_operating_system
    
    Let result1 be assert_not_none with value as detected_os and message as "Operating system should be detected"
    
    Note: Verify it's a known OS or unknown
    Let valid_os be (detected_os is equal to "linux") or (detected_os is equal to "windows") or (detected_os is equal to "macos") or (detected_os is equal to "unknown")
    Let result2 be assert_true with value as valid_os and message as "Detected OS should be valid"
    
    Return result1 and result2

Process called "test_numa_node_detection":
    Note: Tests NUMA node detection and topology discovery
    Let detected_nodes be NUMASupport.detect_nodes
    
    Let result1 be assert_not_none with value as detected_nodes and message as "NUMA nodes should be detected"
    Let result2 be assert_greater_than with actual as length of detected_nodes and expected as 0 and message as "Should detect at least one node"
    
    Note: Verify node structure
    If length of detected_nodes is greater than 0:
        Let first_node be detected_nodes[0]
        Let result3 be assert_greater_than with actual as first_node.node_id and expected as -1 and message as "Node ID should be valid"
        Let result4 be assert_not_none with value as first_node.cpus and message as "Node should have CPUs"
        Let result5 be assert_greater_than with actual as first_node.memory_mb and expected as 0 and message as "Node should have memory"
        Let result6 be assert_not_none with value as first_node.distance_matrix and message as "Node should have distance matrix"
        Let result7 be assert_true with value as first_node.active and message as "Node should be active"
        Return result1 and result2 and result3 and result4 and result5 and result6 and result7
    
    Return result1 and result2

Process called "test_numa_topology_creation":
    Note: Tests NUMA topology creation and validation
    Let topology be NUMASupport.create_numa_topology
    
    Let result1 be assert_not_none with value as topology and message as "NUMA topology should be created"
    Let result2 be assert_greater_than with actual as topology.total_nodes and expected as 0 and message as "Topology should have nodes"
    Let result3 be assert_not_none with value as topology.operating_system and message as "Topology should detect OS"
    Let result4 be assert_greater_than with actual as topology.cpu_count and expected as 0 and message as "Topology should count CPUs"
    Let result5 be assert_greater_than with actual as topology.total_memory_mb and expected as 0 and message as "Topology should calculate total memory"
    Let result6 be assert_greater_than with actual as topology.detection_time and expected as 0 and message as "Topology should record detection time"
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3 and result4 and result5 and result6

Process called "test_fallback_topology_creation":
    Note: Tests fallback topology creation for non-NUMA systems
    Let fallback_topology be NUMASupport.create_single_node_fallback
    
    Let result1 be assert_not_none with value as fallback_topology and message as "Fallback topology should be created"
    Let result2 be assert_equals with actual as length of fallback_topology and expected as 1 and message as "Fallback should have single node"
    
    If length of fallback_topology is greater than 0:
        Let single_node be fallback_topology[0]
        Let result3 be assert_equals with actual as single_node.node_id and expected as 0 and message as "Fallback node should have ID 0"
        Let result4 be assert_greater_than with actual as single_node.memory_mb and expected as 0 and message as "Fallback node should have memory"
        Let result5 be assert_true with value as single_node.active and message as "Fallback node should be active"
        Return result1 and result2 and result3 and result4 and result5
    
    Return result1 and result2

Note: NUMA Memory Allocation Tests

Process called "test_numa_allocator_creation":
    Note: Tests creation of NUMA-aware allocator
    Let topology be create_test_numa_topology
    Let allocator be NUMASupport.create_numa_allocator with node_id as 0 and policy as "local" and topology as topology
    
    Let result1 be assert_not_none with value as allocator and message as "NUMA allocator should be created"
    Let result2 be assert_equals with actual as allocator.node_id and expected as 0 and message as "Allocator should target correct node"
    Let result3 be assert_equals with actual as allocator.allocation_policy and expected as "local" and message as "Allocator should use correct policy"
    Let result4 be assert_not_none with value as allocator.allocated_memory and message as "Allocator should track memory"
    Let result5 be assert_not_none with value as allocator.performance_stats and message as "Allocator should track performance"
    Let result6 be assert_true with value as allocator.thread_safe and message as "Allocator should be thread-safe"
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3 and result4 and result5 and result6

Process called "test_numa_memory_allocation":
    Note: Tests NUMA-aware memory allocation
    Let topology be create_test_numa_topology
    Let allocator be NUMASupport.create_numa_allocator with node_id as 0 and policy as "local" and topology as topology
    
    Let memory_block be NUMASupport.allocate_numa_memory with allocator as allocator and size_mb as TEST_ALLOCATION_SIZE_MB
    
    Let result1 be assert_not_none with value as memory_block and message as "NUMA memory should be allocated"
    Let result2 be assert_equals with actual as memory_block.size_mb and expected as TEST_ALLOCATION_SIZE_MB and message as "Block should have correct size"
    Let result3 be assert_equals with actual as memory_block.node_id and expected as 0 and message as "Block should be on correct node"
    Let result4 be assert_true with value as memory_block.numa_local and message as "Block should be NUMA local"
    Let result5 be assert_greater_than with actual as memory_block.address and expected as 0 and message as "Block should have valid address"
    Let result6 be assert_greater_than with actual as memory_block.allocated_time and expected as 0 and message as "Block should have allocation time"
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3 and result4 and result5 and result6

Process called "test_numa_memory_deallocation":
    Note: Tests NUMA-aware memory deallocation
    Let topology be create_test_numa_topology
    Let allocator be NUMASupport.create_numa_allocator with node_id as 0 and policy as "local" and topology as topology
    
    Let memory_block be NUMASupport.allocate_numa_memory with allocator as allocator and size_mb as TEST_ALLOCATION_SIZE_MB
    Let initial_count be length of allocator.allocated_memory
    
    Let deallocation_result be NUMASupport.deallocate_numa_memory with allocator as allocator and block as memory_block
    
    Let result1 be assert_true with value as deallocation_result and message as "NUMA memory should be deallocated"
    Let result2 be assert_equals with actual as length of allocator.allocated_memory and expected as (initial_count minus 1) and message as "Allocated memory count should decrease"
    
    Return result1 and result2

Process called "test_memory_binding_policies":
    Note: Tests different memory binding policies
    Let topology be create_test_numa_topology
    
    Note: Test local policy
    Let local_allocator be NUMASupport.create_numa_allocator with node_id as 0 and policy as "local" and topology as topology
    Let local_block be NUMASupport.allocate_numa_memory with allocator as local_allocator and size_mb as TEST_ALLOCATION_SIZE_MB
    
    Let result1 be assert_equals with actual as local_block.node_id and expected as 0 and message as "Local policy should allocate on target node"
    
    Note: Test interleave policy
    Let interleave_allocator be NUMASupport.create_numa_allocator with node_id as -1 and policy as "interleave" and topology as topology
    Let interleave_block be NUMASupport.allocate_numa_memory with allocator as interleave_allocator and size_mb as TEST_ALLOCATION_SIZE_MB
    
    Let result2 be assert_not_none with value as interleave_block and message as "Interleave policy should allocate memory"
    
    Note: Test preferred policy
    Let preferred_allocator be NUMASupport.create_numa_allocator with node_id as 1 and policy as "preferred" and topology as topology
    Let preferred_block be NUMASupport.allocate_numa_memory with allocator as preferred_allocator and size_mb as TEST_ALLOCATION_SIZE_MB
    
    Let result3 be assert_not_none with value as preferred_block and message as "Preferred policy should allocate memory"
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3

Note: NUMA Distance and Performance Tests

Process called "test_numa_distance_calculation":
    Note: Tests NUMA distance calculation between nodes
    Let topology be create_test_numa_topology
    
    Note: Test distance from node to itself (should be minimum)
    Let self_distance be NUMASupport.calculate_numa_distance with topology as topology and from_node as 0 and to_node as 0
    Let result1 be assert_equals with actual as self_distance and expected as 10 and message as "Self distance should be minimum (10)"
    
    Note: Test distance between different nodes
    Let cross_distance be NUMASupport.calculate_numa_distance with topology as topology and from_node as 0 and to_node as 1
    Let result2 be assert_greater_than with actual as cross_distance and expected as 10 and message as "Cross-node distance should be greater than self"
    
    Note: Test symmetric distance
    Let reverse_distance be NUMASupport.calculate_numa_distance with topology as topology and from_node as 1 and to_node as 0
    Let result3 be assert_equals with actual as cross_distance and expected as reverse_distance and message as "Distance should be symmetric"
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3

Process called "test_memory_bandwidth_measurement":
    Note: Tests memory bandwidth measurement
    Let topology be create_test_numa_topology
    
    Note: Test bandwidth measurement for each node
    For each node in topology.nodes:
        Let bandwidth be NUMASupport.measure_memory_bandwidth with node_id as node.node_id
        Let result be assert_greater_than with actual as bandwidth and expected as 0 and message as "Bandwidth should be positive for node " plus convert_to_string with value as node.node_id
        If not result:
            Return false
    
    Return true

Process called "test_memory_latency_measurement":
    Note: Tests memory latency measurement
    Let topology be create_test_numa_topology
    
    Note: Test latency measurement for each node
    For each node in topology.nodes:
        Let latency be NUMASupport.measure_memory_latency with node_id as node.node_id
        Let result = assert_greater_than with actual as latency and expected as 0 and message as "Latency should be positive for node " plus convert_to_string with value as node.node_id
        If not result:
            Return false
    
    Return true

Process called "test_performance_monitoring":
    Note: Tests NUMA performance monitoring
    Let topology be create_test_numa_topology
    Let allocator be NUMASupport.create_numa_allocator with node_id as 0 and policy as "local" and topology as topology
    
    Note: Perform allocations to generate performance data
    For i from 0 to 4:
        NUMASupport.allocate_numa_memory with allocator as allocator and size_mb as TEST_ALLOCATION_SIZE_MB
    
    Note: Update performance statistics
    NUMASupport.update_performance_stats with allocator as allocator
    
    Let result1 be assert_greater_than with actual as allocator.performance_stats["allocation_count"] and expected as 0 and message as "Should track allocation count"
    Let result2 be assert_greater_than with actual as allocator.performance_stats["total_allocated_mb"] and expected as 0 and message as "Should track total allocated memory"
    Let result3 be assert_not_none with value as allocator.performance_stats["average_allocation_time"] and message as "Should track allocation time"
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3

Note: NUMA Memory Migration Tests

Process called "test_memory_migration_cost_calculation":
    Note: Tests memory migration cost calculation
    Let topology be create_test_numa_topology
    Let memory_block be create_test_memory_block with node_id as 0 and size_mb as TEST_ALLOCATION_SIZE_MB
    
    Note: Calculate migration cost to same node (should be zero)
    Let same_node_cost be NUMASupport.calculate_migration_cost with block as memory_block and target_node as 0 and topology as topology
    Let result1 be assert_equals with actual as same_node_cost and expected as 0 and message as "Same node migration cost should be zero"
    
    Note: Calculate migration cost to different node
    Let cross_node_cost be NUMASupport.calculate_migration_cost with block as memory_block and target_node as 1 and topology as topology
    Let result2 be assert_greater_than with actual as cross_node_cost and expected as 0 and message as "Cross-node migration should have cost"
    
    Note: Larger blocks should have higher migration costs
    Let large_block be create_test_memory_block with node_id as 0 and size_mb as TEST_ALLOCATION_SIZE_MB multiplied by 4
    Let large_migration_cost be NUMASupport.calculate_migration_cost with block as large_block and target_node as 1 and topology as topology
    Let result3 be assert_greater_than with actual as large_migration_cost and expected as cross_node_cost and message as "Larger blocks should cost more to migrate"
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3

Process called "test_memory_migration_execution":
    Note: Tests actual memory migration between NUMA nodes
    Let topology be create_test_numa_topology
    Let allocator be NUMASupport.create_numa_allocator with node_id as 0 and policy as "local" and topology as topology
    
    Let memory_block be NUMASupport.allocate_numa_memory with allocator as allocator and size_mb as TEST_ALLOCATION_SIZE_MB
    Let original_node be memory_block.node_id
    
    Note: Migrate memory to different node
    Let migration_result be NUMASupport.migrate_memory with block as memory_block and target_node as 1 and topology as topology
    
    Let result1 be assert_true with value as migration_result.success and message as "Memory migration should succeed"
    Let result2 be assert_equals with actual as memory_block.node_id and expected as 1 and message as "Block should be on target node after migration"
    Let result3 be assert_not_equals with actual as memory_block.node_id and expected as original_node and message as "Block should have moved from original node"
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3

Process called "test_migration_threshold_optimization":
    Note: Tests migration threshold optimization
    Let topology be create_test_numa_topology
    
    Note: Test with block below migration threshold
    Let small_block be create_test_memory_block with node_id as 0 and size_mb as 16
    Let should_migrate_small be NUMASupport.should_migrate_memory with block as small_block and target_node as 1 and topology as topology and threshold as TEST_MIGRATION_THRESHOLD
    
    Note: Test with block above migration threshold
    Let large_block be create_test_memory_block with node_id as 0 and size_mb as 256
    Let should_migrate_large be NUMASupport.should_migrate_memory with block as large_block and target_node as 1 and topology as topology and threshold as TEST_MIGRATION_THRESHOLD
    
    Let result1 be assert_not_none with value as should_migrate_small and message as "Should evaluate small block migration"
    Let result2 be assert_not_none with value as should_migrate_large and message as "Should evaluate large block migration"
    
    Note: Migration decision should consider block size and cost
    Return result1 and result2

Note: NUMA GC Integration Tests

Process called "test_numa_gc_algorithm_creation":
    Note: Tests creation of NUMA-aware garbage collection algorithm
    Let topology be create_test_numa_topology
    Let numa_gc be NUMASupport.create_numa_gc_algorithm with algorithm_type as "generational" and target_nodes as list containing 0, 1 and policy as "node_local" and topology as topology
    
    Let result1 be assert_not_none with value as numa_gc and message as "NUMA GC algorithm should be created"
    Let result2 be assert_equals with actual as numa_gc.algorithm_type and expected as "generational" and message as "GC should use correct algorithm type"
    Let result3 be assert_contains with collection as numa_gc.target_nodes and item as 0 and message as "GC should target specified nodes"
    Let result4 be assert_equals with actual as numa_gc.gc_policy and expected as "node_local" and message as "GC should use correct policy"
    Let result5 be assert_not_none with value as numa_gc.performance_metrics and message as "GC should track performance metrics"
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3 and result4 and result5

Process called "test_numa_gc_collection_optimization":
    Note: Tests NUMA-aware garbage collection optimization
    Let topology be create_test_numa_topology
    Let numa_gc be NUMASupport.create_numa_gc_algorithm with algorithm_type as "mark_sweep" and target_nodes as list containing 0, 1, 2 and policy as "interleave" and topology as topology
    
    Note: Simulate GC collection on specific nodes
    Let collection_result be NUMASupport.run_numa_gc_collection with gc as numa_gc and target_nodes as list containing 0, 1
    
    Let result1 be assert_true with value as collection_result.success and message as "NUMA GC collection should succeed"
    Let result2 be assert_greater_than with actual as collection_result.objects_collected and expected as 0 and message as "Should collect objects"
    Let result3 be assert_greater_than with actual as collection_result.memory_reclaimed_mb and expected as 0 and message as "Should reclaim memory"
    Let result4 be assert_not_none with value as collection_result.performance_stats and message as "Should provide performance statistics"
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3 and result4

Process called "test_numa_gc_performance_monitoring":
    Note: Tests NUMA GC performance monitoring
    Let topology be create_test_numa_topology
    Let numa_gc be NUMASupport.create_numa_gc_algorithm with algorithm_type as "copying" and target_nodes as list containing 0, 1, 2, 3 and policy as "preferred" and topology as topology
    
    Note: Run multiple collections to gather statistics
    For i from 0 to 4:
        NUMASupport.run_numa_gc_collection with gc as numa_gc and target_nodes as list containing (i modulo 4)
    
    Note: Update performance metrics
    NUMASupport.update_numa_gc_metrics with gc as numa_gc
    
    Let result1 be assert_greater_than with actual as numa_gc.collection_stats["total_collections"] and expected as 0 and message as "Should track total collections"
    Let result2 be assert_greater_than with actual as numa_gc.performance_metrics["average_collection_time"] and expected as 0.0 and message as "Should track collection time"
    Let result3 be assert_not_none with value as numa_gc.performance_metrics["memory_efficiency"] and message as "Should track memory efficiency"
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3

Note: Error Handling and Edge Case Tests

Process called "test_numa_error_handling":
    Note: Tests NUMA error handling for various failure scenarios
    Let topology be create_test_numa_topology
    
    Note: Test invalid node ID
    Try:
        NUMASupport.create_numa_allocator with node_id as 999 and policy as "local" and topology as topology
        Let result1 be false
    Catch error:
        Let result1 be true
    
    Note: Test invalid allocation size
    Let allocator be NUMASupport.create_numa_allocator with node_id as 0 and policy as "local" and topology as topology
    Try:
        NUMASupport.allocate_numa_memory with allocator as allocator and size_mb as -1
        Let result2 be false
    Catch error:
        Let result2 be true
    
    Note: Test migration to invalid node
    Let memory_block be create_test_memory_block with node_id as 0 and size_mb as TEST_ALLOCATION_SIZE_MB
    Try:
        NUMASupport.migrate_memory with block as memory_block and target_node as 999 and topology as topology
        Let result3 be false
    Catch error:
        Let result3 be true
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3

Process called "test_non_numa_system_fallback":
    Note: Tests graceful fallback on non-NUMA systems
    Note: Simulate non-NUMA system by creating empty topology
    Let non_numa_topology be NUMASupport.NUMATopology with:
        nodes as list containing
        total_nodes as 0
        numa_available as false
        operating_system as "test_os"
        cpu_count as 1
        total_memory_mb as 1024
        interleave_policy as "none"
        detection_time as Common.get_current_timestamp
        metadata as dictionary containing
    
    Let fallback_nodes be NUMASupport.handle_numa_fallback with topology as non_numa_topology
    
    Let result1 be assert_not_none with value as fallback_nodes and message as "Fallback should provide nodes"
    Let result2 be assert_equals with actual as length of fallback_nodes and expected as 1 and message as "Fallback should provide single node"
    
    If length of fallback_nodes is greater than 0:
        Let fallback_node be fallback_nodes[0]
        Let result3 be assert_equals with actual as fallback_node.node_id and expected as 0 and message as "Fallback node should have ID 0"
        Let result4 be assert_true with value as fallback_node.active and message as "Fallback node should be active"
        Return result1 and result2 and result3 and result4
    
    Return result1 and result2

Process called "test_concurrent_numa_operations":
    Note: Tests thread safety of concurrent NUMA operations
    Let topology be create_test_numa_topology
    Let allocator = NUMASupport.create_numa_allocator with node_id as 0 and policy as "local" and topology as topology
    
    Note: Simulate concurrent allocations
    Let concurrent_blocks be list containing
    For i from 0 to 9:
        Let block be NUMASupport.allocate_numa_memory with allocator as allocator and size_mb as TEST_ALLOCATION_SIZE_MB
        Add block to concurrent_blocks
    
    Let result1 be assert_equals with actual as length of concurrent_blocks and expected as 10 and message as "All concurrent allocations should succeed"
    Let result2 be assert_equals with actual as length of allocator.allocated_memory and expected as 10 and message as "Allocator should track all concurrent allocations"
    
    Note: Simulate concurrent deallocations
    For each block in concurrent_blocks:
        NUMASupport.deallocate_numa_memory with allocator as allocator and block as block
    
    Let result3 be assert_equals with actual as length of allocator.allocated_memory and expected as 0 and message as "All memory should be deallocated"
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3

Note: AI/Agent Integration Tests

Process called "test_ai_numa_optimization_api":
    Note: Tests AI-friendly NUMA optimization APIs
    Let topology be create_test_numa_topology
    
    Note: Generate AI optimization recommendations
    Let ai_recommendations be NUMASupport.generate_numa_ai_recommendations with topology as topology
    
    Let result1 be assert_not_none with value as ai_recommendations and message as "AI recommendations should be generated"
    Let result2 be assert_not_none with value as ai_recommendations["memory_optimization"] and message as "Should include memory optimization"
    Let result3 be assert_not_none with value as ai_recommendations["allocation_strategy"] and message as "Should include allocation strategy"
    Let result4 be assert_not_none with value as ai_recommendations["migration_opportunities"] and message as "Should include migration opportunities"
    Let result5 be assert_not_none with value as ai_recommendations["performance_tuning"] and message as "Should include performance tuning"
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3 and result4 and result5

Process called "test_agent_numa_monitoring":
    Note: Tests agent-driven NUMA monitoring
    Let topology be create_test_numa_topology
    
    Note: Set up agent monitoring configuration
    Let monitoring_config be dictionary containing
        "agent_id" as "numa_monitor_agent"
        "monitoring_interval" as 1000
        "optimization_thresholds" as dictionary containing
            "cross_node_allocation_ratio" as 0.3
            "migration_frequency" as 10
            "memory_imbalance_ratio" as 0.4
        "actions" as list containing "rebalance", "migrate", "optimize"
    
    Let monitoring_result be NUMASupport.run_agent_numa_monitoring with topology as topology and config as monitoring_config
    
    Let result1 be assert_not_none with value as monitoring_result and message as "Agent monitoring should produce results"
    Let result2 be assert_not_none with value as monitoring_result["agent_id"] and message as "Should include agent ID"
    Let result3 be assert_not_none with value as monitoring_result["topology_health"] and message as "Should assess topology health"
    Let result4 be assert_not_none with value as monitoring_result["optimization_actions"] and message as "Should suggest optimization actions"
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3 and result4

Note: Performance Benchmark Tests

Process called "test_numa_allocation_performance":
    Note: Tests performance benchmarks for NUMA allocation
    Let topology be create_test_numa_topology
    Let allocator be NUMASupport.create_numa_allocator with node_id as 0 and policy as "local" and topology as topology
    
    Note: Benchmark allocation performance
    Let start_time be Common.get_current_timestamp
    For i from 0 to 99:
        NUMASupport.allocate_numa_memory with allocator as allocator and size_mb as 32
    Let end_time be Common.get_current_timestamp
    Let allocation_time be end_time minus start_time
    
    Let result1 be assert_less_than with actual as allocation_time and expected as 5000 and message as "100 allocations should complete in under 5 seconds"
    
    Note: Calculate allocation rate
    Let allocation_rate be 100000.0 divided by allocation_time
    Let result2 be assert_greater_than with actual as allocation_rate and expected as 10.0 and message as "Should achieve reasonable allocation rate"
    
    Return result1 and result2

Process called "test_numa_migration_performance":
    Note: Tests performance benchmarks for memory migration
    Let topology be create_test_numa_topology
    Let allocator be NUMASupport.create_numa_allocator with node_id as 0 and policy as "local" and topology as topology
    
    Note: Create blocks to migrate
    Let blocks_to_migrate be list containing
    For i from 0 to 9:
        Let block be NUMASupport.allocate_numa_memory with allocator as allocator and size_mb as 64
        Add block to blocks_to_migrate
    
    Note: Benchmark migration performance
    Let start_time be Common.get_current_timestamp
    For each block in blocks_to_migrate:
        NUMASupport.migrate_memory with block as block and target_node as 1 and topology as topology
    Let end_time be Common.get_current_timestamp
    Let migration_time be end_time minus start_time
    
    Let result1 be assert_less_than with actual as migration_time and expected as 10000 and message as "10 migrations should complete in under 10 seconds"
    
    Return result1

